<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="prof" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Instructor Information</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>Hi! My name is Anansa Green, and my pronouns are she/her. Please address me as Mrs. Green and be sure to let me know if I mispronounce your name or if you would like to be called something other than what is on the roster. Click below to view a brief (approx. 1.5 min) intro video to help you get to know me a little (no sound needed).</p>
  </introduction>
<video youtube="CXfsFyWg9cU" width="50%">
</video>

<section xml:id="philosophy">
  <title>Teaching Philosophy</title>
  <p>My philosophy of teaching can be summarized by the following statements:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          <em>Anyone</em> can get better at <em>anything</em> with consistent and effective effort.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Questions are <em>always</em> welcomed and encouraged.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Mistakes are expected, inspected, and respected.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          <em>Problem-solving</em> is what you do when you don't know what to do.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>

<section xml:id="contact">
  <title>Contact Information</title>
  <p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Phone: (432) 685-6803
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Email: <email>agreen@midland.edu</email>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Office: MHAB 121
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <subsection xml:id="pref-method">
    <title>Preferred Method</title>
    <p>
      Please note that <em>I prefer to be contacted through Canvas inbox messages</em> for a variety of reasons.</p>
      <p>Before sending your message:
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Include a <em>2-3 word subject</em> that summarizes your request or question topic.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If you are messaging about a specific assignment, please <em>use the name of the assignment</em> as it appears in Canvas.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If you are messaging about a technical issue, <em>screenshots help</em> me understand exactly what you are describing and often help us avoid going back and forth. If you need help taking a screenshot, you may find this <url href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/gofullpage-full-page-scre/fdpohaocaechififmbbbbbknoalclacl">Chrome browser extension></url> useful.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If you choose to email me through my MC (Midland College) email address, please be sure to <em>include your name and course</em>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            NOTE: All discussions involving <em>personal information</em> (grades, attendance, etc.) <em>must</em> go through an <em>official MC</em> communication channel - either your @mail.midland.edu <em>student email</em> or <em>Canvas inbox</em> messages.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </subsection>
</section>
